rComments: Anne is the BESTBESTBEST. If you had even the slightest interest in museums or art, TAKE THIS CLASS. You essentially volunteer at Krannert Art Museum. Classes are essentially discussion-based or prep for events at the museum. Also, Anne is extremely funny. It's a very fun class. Take it before you're a senior!!! so you can keep volunteering!
Sautman is a great person and a good facilitator, also knowledgeable about the museum business as well.

I can't say enough great things about Professor Sautman. Her Museums in Action class is probably one of the best I've taken. Anne is really cool and has a ton of art museum experience, but she also trusts students to stay involved and get the job done (You get to plan and lead events and tours for the Krannert Art Museum). Grading is very fair too.
